        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 4:45AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 445 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
northwestern Montgomery, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Montgomery, Prattville, Millbrook, Wetumpka, Tallassee, Milstead,
Pike Road, Elmore, Coosada, Deatsville, Shorter, Montgomery Zoo,
Boylston, Hyundai Motors Of Alabama, Auburn University In Montgomery,
Bob Woodruff Lake, Woodcrest, Emerald Mountain, Maxwell Air Force
Base, and Waugh.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
